JOHANNESBURG – South African actor, television presenter Akhumzi Jezile has died. Jezile’s career flourished when he was presenter on various YOTV shows on SABC1, from 2007 to 2012. Akhumzi was also a radio presenter for Umhlobo Wenene for SABC. Various reports claim that Akhumzi died in an apparent accident. Minister of Arts and Culture Nathi Mthethwa paid tribute to him on twitter. South African fans are shocked by his sudden death. The police are yet to release a statement on the cause of death. *Editor’s Note: This is a developing story, more to follow. eNCA